<HEADLINE> China Provides Loan to Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- China and Bangladesh Sunday signed a
loan agreement here to provide another 100 million RMB yuan (12
million U.S. dollars) to Bangladesh for building the Bangabandhu
International Convention Center.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed during the visit of an 11-member
Chinese delegation headed by Wei Jianguo, assistant minister of
the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation of China on
April 2-4.
</P>
<P>
The government of the People's Republic of China agreed in 1998
to provide 200 million yuan (24 million dollars) interest-free
loan to Bangladesh for construction of the Bangabandhu
International Conference Center in Dhaka, and the loan agreement
for the first 100 million yuan was signed on January 21, 1999 in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project will be 2 billion taka (40
million dollars) of which the Chinese government will provide 24
million dollars in grant and interest-free loan. The rest will
come from the Bangladeshi government.
</P>
<P>
The facilities of the convention center will include 570 seats
for representatives in the plenary hall, 100 seats for observers,
1,000 seats for visitors, two 280-seat conference rooms and a 700-
seat banquet hall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
