<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Celebrates International Cricket Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh Sunday celebrated the
International Cricket Week from April 2 to 8 designated by the
International Cricket Council (ICC) to be observed all over the
world in association with the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The celebrations were kicked off with a colorful rally in Dhaka
city at 8 AM, which ended at the Bangbandhu National Stadium, the
venue for a match between Asia XI and World XI on April 8th, the
closing day of the Week.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh, as a very prospective cricket-playing nation, earns
the ICC priority in its development program worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) is all set to make the most of
the occasion by holding different ICC-designed programs throughout
the week.
</P>
<P>
On April 3, Bangladesh will host a series of matches among the
under-10 cricketers. A quiz competition and a seminar on "Cricket,
Patriotism and Globalization" will be held on April 4. Extensive
development programs in six divisional headquarters and a painting
competition of the children will be held on April 6 and 7
respectively.
</P>
<P>
As part of its game's globalization drive, the ICC in
cooperation with the United Nations is holding various programs to
introduce cricket to new audiences around the world, as well as
providing entertainment for those familiar with the game.
</P>
<P>
In his message on the Week, U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan
expressed his happiness to join cricket fans in celebrating
Cricket Week.
</P>
<P>
"We can share our joy in everything we love about the game: its
grace and subtlety, and the premium it puts on sportsmanship, team
spirit, and fair play," Annan said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
