<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fiji Wins Tokyo Leg of World Sevens Rugby </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Fiji beat New Zealand 27-22 to win
the Tokyo leg of the World Sevens Rugby Series here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Including the tournament, the ninth of the 10-city inaugural
series, Fiji has collected 172 points in the rankings from five
tour events and New Zealand got 166 from four.
</P>
<P>
Japan beat France 12-7 to win the Plate event for teams that
failed to advance to the semi-finals of the main championship.
</P>
<P>
In the Bowl competition for teams that finished lower in the
preliminary rounds, Samoa outscored South Korea 19-12.
</P>
<P>
The final leg will be played in Paris on May 27-28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
