<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Germans Killed by Burglars in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A German family of four were
killed today in Nanjing, capital of east China's Jiangsu province
by four burglars who broke into their residence.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place in the early hours today, when 51-year-
old Juergen Pfrang found the thieves in his house, struggled
against them, and was killed.
</P>
<P>
Pfrang was deputy general manager of Yaxing-Benz, a Sino-German
automotive joint venture in Yangzhou, Jiangsu. His wife, son and
daughter were also killed.
</P>
<P>
The murderers were arrested on the spot by police, who rushed
to the scene after receiving a report from guards of the
residential area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
