<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Leaders Visit Exhibitions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Top Chinese leaders Jiang Zemin,
Hu Jintao and Li Lanqing visited an exhibition on respecting
science and fighting against superstition here Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition features photos, videos, and models that expose
the true face of Falun Gong and other cults which use
pseudoscience and superstition to cheat the people.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin said that the exhibition was well
organized and would help people understand the danger of the Falun
Gong cult. He also pointed out that it would help improve people's
ethical level and scientific awareness.
</P>
<P>
Some 100,000 people have visited the exhibition which is being
held at the Chinese People's Revolutionary Military Museum.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and other Chinese leaders also visited an exhibition on
China's latest patented technologies sponsored by the State
Intellectual Property Office at the same museum.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called on the nation to support patent work and bring the
patent system into full play, and urged people to produce
marketable high-technologies with the intellectual property rights
of their own in an effort to boost the economy.
</P>
<P>
Central and local patent administrations from 31 provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions, and eight ministries and
corporations have sent representatives to the five-day exhibition.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
