<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strike Paralyzes Costa Rican Ports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At Limon port, on the Caribbean coast, the strikers prevent
loading and unloading, as well as the entry of vehicles into the
port.
</P>
<P>
The strike is spreading to Costarican Petroleum Refinery and
the provision of fuel may be affected if it goes on.
</P>
<P>
The strikers intend to force the government to withdraw a
polemic law project that breaks state monopoly in
telecommunications and increases private participation in the
energy sector.
</P>
<P>
For 15 days, workers have held on to the strike. University
students and supporters, peasants and other sectors joined the
strike.  
</P>
</TEXT>
