<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat to Meet Clinton Late This Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian President Yasser
Arafat will hold talks with U.S. President Bill Clinton and
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright late this month, mainly
focusing on "final status" negotiations between Israel and the
Palestinians, the State Department said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
No dates have been set for Arafat's visit. He last met Clinton
in Davos, Switzerland, in January.
</P>
<P>
Israel and the Palestinian has set the date of September 13 as
the deadline for an a final status agreement, which would deal
many difficult issues, such as borders, Jerusalem, Palestinian
refugees and Jewish settlements.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, lower-level Israeli-Palestinian talks will resume at
Bolling Air Force Base near Washington on Thursday after an eight-
day break, State Department spokesman James Rubin said.
</P>
<P>
"We expect them to be intensive, substantive, carrying forward
from what they discussed in the past. It's a little early to
speculate on exactly what will be happen but we do expect an
intense set of discussions," he told reporters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
