<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peru to Export Liquid Gas to Chile, Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Peru will supply liquid gas to the
Chilean and Ecuadoran markets, Minister of Energy and Mines Jorge
Chambot said Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Liquids and condensations of Camisea gas deposit, discovered
in Peru's Amazon, will be exported from the first day of placing
in action of this project, programmed for the year 2003," said the
official.
</P>
<P>
With this purpose a trans-Andean gas pipeline will be built and
parallelly a housing estate will be constructed in Chincha, a
coastal city from which it'll be exported by sea, said Chambot.
</P>
<P>
According to Chambot, Peru is deficient in liquid petroleum gas
(LPG). However, it will be reversed once the Camisea deposit
enters into operation and it could even be exported to other
countries.
</P>
<P>
"In my opinion, there'll be a big international market for this
kind of project, mainly to Korea and Japan, as well as the United
States' west coast," he affirmed.
</P>
<P>
The international contest for transporting and distributing gas
will take place in May, whereby the closure of contracts for
concessions will be in June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
