<HEADLINE> Zanzibar's Treason Case to Be Tried Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The High Court of Zanzibar
announced on Monday that hearing of the treason case involving 18
opposition Civic United Front (CUF) activists will officially
begin on May 2 this year.
</P>
<P>
The High Court Judge Garba Tumaka denied bail application to
the suspects due to the seriousness, nature and gravity of the
offence.
</P>
<P>
The 18 defendants have been in remand prison since they were
arrested in 1997 on charges they conspired to overthrow President
Salmin Amour of the semi-autonomous Zanzibar island in the Indian
Ocean off mainland Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Zanzibar joined mainland Tanzania to form the United Republic
of Tanzania after a revolt in 1964 that ousted the sultan and
Omani Arabs who ruled the island. 
</P>
</TEXT>
