<HEADLINE> Iran's Non-Oil Export Enjoy 6.1 Percent Boost Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Iran's non-oil export enjoyed a 6.1
percent increase in the past Iranian calendar year which ended on
March 19 to reach 3.1 billion U.S. dollars, Iran's Customs unveiled
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In a preliminary report, the Customs said that over 112 million
dollars of the export constituted cross border transactions and 121
million dollars was in the form of carry-on luggage exported to
various countries, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Export of rugs last Iranian year were valued at 686 million
dollars, constituting 22.7 percent of the total non-oil export on
the top of the list of export items, it said.
</P>
<P>
Other main non-oil export included chemicals valued at 333
million dollars, pistachios at 315 million dollars, ironware and
steel at 172 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Iran has made desperate efforts in the past decade to boost its
non-oil export with an aim to reducing its dependence on oil
revenues, which accounted for more than 80 percent of the country's
badly-needed hard currencies.
</P>
<P>
However, with the economic stagnation both in Iran and other
countries in recent years, Iran failed to reach the target of
fetching more than 5 billion dollars annually from non-oil export
set by its second five-year development plan (1995-2000).
</P>
<P>
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami announced an adjustment plan
in 1998 to boost domestic production in order to save the
country's "ailing economy." However, the country failed to make a
desirable development in non-oil sectors due to white-hot factional
struggles, bureaucratic procedures and lack of foreign investments.
</P>
<P>
According to the Iranian Customs, the country's import last
Iranian year amounted to 13.2 billion dollars, showing a decrease
of 8.4 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Machinery, industrial and electric appliances, ironware, wheat,
chemicals and cooking oil were the main imported goods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
