<HEADLINE> URGENT European Plane in Baghdad to Protest U.N. Embargo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, April 3 (Xinhua) -- An airplane carrying three persons
from France and Italy landed at the Al-Rashed military airport in
Baghdad at 19:45 p.m. local time (1645 GMT), to protest the decade-
long U.N. embargo imposed on Iraq.
</P>
<P>
At the airport, Jean-Marie Benjamin, head of the delegation,
read a declaration to the local and foreign media who have been
waiting for more than seven hours.
</P>
