<HEADLINE> French Police Seize Large Amount of False Bills of U.S. Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 3 (Xinhua) -- French police seized last week a
large amount of false bills of U.S. dollar and arrested two men
accused of smuggling the false bills, reported Agence France-
Presse on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Police arrested last Wednesday a man who had a suitcase
containing 2 million U.S. dollars in false bills and a
unregistered pistol in his car.
</P>
<P>
The man, described as a French citizen of Portuguese origin,
said he bought the false bills in Lisbon from another Portuguese
who also lived in Paris.
</P>
<P>
Police then arrested the seller of the false bills on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
French officials said that the false bills came from Spain and
were seen before in France. 
</P>
