<HEADLINE> British Catalogue Exhibition Opens in Nairobi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A British catalogue exhibition
involving more than 70 companies was opened here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition "Britain in East Africa", unlike the traditional
one with a display of products and equipment, just showcases the
catalogues detailing the products and services of the British
companies, which saves on costs that could have been directed to
shipment and exhibition.
</P>
<P>
The participants are from financial, manufacturing,
agricultural, horticultural, electronic, education, health and
Information technology sectors, said the Promoter Exhibitions,
the organizer of the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Dave Howells, the operation manager of the Promoter
Exhibitions, said through the catalogues, potential trading
partners and customers could select the firms which have their
products requirements to deal with.
</P>
<P>
Similarly, east African firms will also be able to select
British companies to whom they could market their products,
Howells added.
</P>
<P>
After the two-day display in Kenya, the exhibition will move to
Uganda's capital Kampala and run on April 13 and 14, and finally
will take place in the Tanzanian capital Dar es Salaam on April
27 and 28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
