<HEADLINE> Iran Produces 6.3 Million Tons of Steel Last Fiscal year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Iran produced over 6.3 million tons
of unprocessed steel in the past Iranian fiscal year which ended on
March 19, an official from the National Iranian Steel Company
(NISC) announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Managing Director of the NISC for Plan and Budget Affairs
Musa Aqa Lankarani said the steel output was three percent higher
than the company's projection, marking a 12 percent increase from
the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Lankarani said more than 5.299 million tons of steel products
were produced at Iranian steel complexes during the year, showing a
rise of 18 percent from the previous year, the Islamic Republic
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
During the period, more than 996,990 tons of steel products
worth 156 million U.S. dollars were exported, he said, adding 660,
000 tons out of the export consignment were steel slabs produced in
southwestern province of Khuzestan.
</P>
<P>
Iran has made desperate efforts in boosting its steel industry
since former Iranian President Hashemi Rafsanjani came to power in
1989, making the country the largest steel producer in the Middle
East.
</P>
<P>
Iran's current steel production capacity was reported at seven
million tons annually and officials said that the country hopes to
raise its steel production capacity to 14.7 million tons by the end
of its third five-year development plan (2000-2005).
</P>
<P>
Lankarani also put the total amount of iron-ore output in the
year at more than 6.9 million tons, or 86 percent of the 8.1
million-ton target.
</P>
<P>
About 165,278 tons of processed minerals were produced in the
country last Iranian year, meeting 97 percent of the target, he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
