<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi has stated that in the new Iranian year starting on March
20 Iran will follow the policy of building confidence with other
countries, the Gulf states in particular.
</P>
<P>
"Iran's detente policy completed its due course in the last
Iranian year and is now in the process of confidence building with
other countries," Kharrazi told envoys and representatives of
foreign countries and international organizations on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He said Tehran is determined to expand and consolidate ties with
all countries on the basis of mutual respect, the Islamic Republic
News Agency reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Iran, which started the detente policy after the moderate
President Mohammad Khatami came to power in August 1997, succeeded
in breaking the political isolation of the United States by
improving relations with its neighbors and the European countries.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi also briefed the audience of Iran's diplomatic
activities at the international level, inside the Organization of
the Islamic Conference under its chairmanship and Tehran's efforts
to strengthen the organization.
</P>
<P>
He said the most important achievements in the domestic scene
last Iranian year were the municipal elections and the February 18
sixth Majlis (parliament) elections, in which Iranian reformists
won overwhelming victories over the powerful conservatives.
</P>
<P>
The elections indicated establishment and institutionalization
of democracy in Iran and serve as an important backbone for the
system and the country, he added. 
</P>
