<HEADLINE> France to Designate Ambassador for Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 3 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin
said on Monday that France will designate soon an ambassador for
environment and will propose the creation of a global organization
for regulating economic development to reinforce environment
protection.
</P>
<P>
In a speech on environment protection and territorial
management at the Sorbonne University, Jospin said that the time
has come for the world to have global regulations for development.
</P>
<P>
``We should engage ourselves in this without delay... France is
ready to bring this question in the international debate to be
held in 2002,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
Jospin said that the regulations for development and
environment protection should be based on ``negotiated and fair
compromises'' to be reached by different countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that European countries should first of all start the
process by establishing an informal mechanism of dialogue among
associations, enterprises, scientists and public decision-makers.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the government should seek support from the
general public as well as enterprises in this field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
