<HEADLINE> Greek Traffic Accidents Kill 130 in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A total of 130 people were killed
and 2,192 injured, including 319 seriously, in traffic accidents
across Greece in January this year, the National Statistics
Service (NSS) announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
In the same month of last year, 149 people lost their lives
and 2,404 were injured in the country's traffic accidents.
</P>
<P>
Greece's traffic accident rate is among the highest in the 15-
member European Union (EU) countries, with more than 2,000 people
killed and 30,000 others injured annually in accidents. 
