<HEADLINE> hke-- Thai Moves On in Asian Boxing Olympic Qualifiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Local hero Wijan Ponlid's victory
Monday boosted the morale of the Thai team on the third day of the
Asian boxing Olympic qualifying tournament here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's reigning Southeast Asian Games bantamweight champion
Wijan gave no chance to his rival, Syria's Shehan Yaser, winning
the flyweight category fight with an impressive 11-0 mark.
</P>
<P>
Wijan shed his weight to suit for the flyweight category and
replace a retired boxer.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday will see the quarter-final bouts of the tournament
while semi-finals will follow on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Participators will have a day to rest on Thursday before
fighting for the remaining 26 out of the 68 berths allocated to
Asia for the Olympiad 2000.
</P>
<P>
Over 200 pugilists from 31 countries and regions are competing
in the Bangkok event, which is the third and last leg of the
qualifying tournament in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Some 42 boxers have successfully made their way to the Sydney
Games in the two earlier legs in Tashkent and Seoul respectively.
</P>
