<HEADLINE> Beijing To Encourage Risk Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's Mayor Liu Qi today told
a group of business people who are attending an international
seminar that overseas investors are encouraged to establish risk
investment funds in the city.
</P>
<P>
Liu said the Chinese capital will see booming development in
the fields of risk investment, Internet technology and electronic
business.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has kicked off a massive project to increase investment
in its Zhongguancun area, one of the country's demonstration zones
for high-tech industry.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has set up three risk investment funds for high-tech
enterprises in the area, known as China's "Silicon Valley", he
said, adding that three more such risk investment funds will be
set up this year.
</P>
<P>
Zhongguancun, located in northwest Beijing, is home to nearly 5,
000 private high-tech businesses, and dozens of academies and
research institutes.
</P>
<P>
The city will set up an exchange center for property rights of
high-tech findings in Zhongguancun, the mayor said, adding that
this center will be part of an effort to speed up the development
of the Zhongguancun area and attract more domestic and overseas
investment to the city's high-tech industry.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of experts and entrepreneurs from a dozen countries
and regions are attending the ongoing "International Seminar on
China Risk Investment, Internet and E-Business."  
</P>
</TEXT>
