<HEADLINE> China Attaches Great Importance to Murders of Germans: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- China will deal with the case
concerning the murders of four Germans Sunday morning in this
capital city of east China's Jiangsu Province strictly in
accordance with the law, a local official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Yang Bu'er, director of the Foreign Affairs Office of the
Jiangsu government, told Xinhua that after the incident the
provincial government immediately contacted the German consulate
in Shanghai and informed them of it.
</P>
<P>
He said that leading officials of both the Jiangsu provincial
government and Nanjing city government attach great importance to
the case, and asked legal departments to make sure the culprits
are punished.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Jiangsu Province has always paid great attention
to security work around the residential areas where foreigners
live, and the government will adopt more effective measures to
protect foreigners' lives and properties.
</P>
<P>
In the early hours of April 2 four farmers broke into the
residence in Nanjing where Pfrang Juren Hermann and his wife and
two children lives. The family of four were all killed when they
disturbed the burglars.
</P>
<P>
Hermann was the deputy general manager of Yaxing-Benz, a Sino-
German automotive joint venture in Yangzhou, Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The murderers were arrested on the spot by police, who rushed
to the scene after receiving a report from guards at the
residential area.
</P>
