<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Border Blaze Extinguished </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A prairie fire which had been
creeping into China from Mongolia since Sunday was put out this
morning, according to the Agriculture Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out on March 27 in an area of grassland of
Mongolia some 80 km north of the Chinese border. At 16:20 pm on
April 2, it entered the Hulun Buir League in China's Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region and created a serious threat.
</P>
<P>
The local government mobilized a large number of firefighters,
who finally succeeded in putting out the fire at 2:15 am today.
</P>
<P>
However, the ministry said that another fire is still raging
along the Sino-Mongolian border. Leading officials of the ministry
have flown to Inner Mongolia to oversee the fire-precaution work
there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
