<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Assistant FM Meets German Diplomat on Murder Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Assistant Foreign Minister
Ma Canrong had a meeting with Herbert Jess, charge d'affaires ad
interim of the German embassy in China this afternoon, to express
deep condolences on the murders of the family of Pfrang Jurgen
Hermann in the early hours of Sunday in Nanjing.
</P>
<P>
Ma also expressed sincere solicitude to the relatives of the
deceased, saying that Pfrang Jurgen Hermann was highly appreciated
by relevant Chinese departments because of his positive efforts
and major contributions to Sino-German economic and technological
cooperation over the years.
</P>
<P>
Ma added he hoped that the incident would not affect the normal
operation of Sino-German economic and technological cooperation.
The Chinese side would like to cooperate with the German side to
effectively handle the problems arising from the incident.
</P>
<P>
The victims, including Pfrang Jurgen Hermann, deputy general
manager of Yaxing-Benz, a Sino-German automotive joint venture in
the city of Yangzhou in Jiangsu Province, and his wife, son and
daughter, were killed in their house in what is thought to have
been a burglary.
</P>
<P>
Four suspects in the case, who are from Shuyang County in east
China's Jiangsu Province, have been arrested and have confessed to
the murders.
</P>
<P>
China's judicial departments will severely punish the murderers
according to the law. Relevant departments of Jiangsu and Nanjing
have informed German General Consulate in Shanghai of the progress
of the investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
