<HEADLINE> China's Biggest Sewage Plant Up to ISO9002 Standards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Gaobeidian Sewage Treatment
Plant in eastern Beijing, the largest of its kind in China, is up
to the internationally recognized quality control standard system
ISO9002.
</P>
<P>
A recent appraisal of the system has shown that the plant is
up to the ISO9002 standards, a stringent international control
system, according to officials with the State Environmental
Protection Administration (SEPA).
</P>
<P>
Located in the eastern suburbs of Beijing, the plant can handle
about 40 percent of the one million tons of sewage discharged
daily in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The plant has recently adopted the IS09002 system to ensure
that the quality of its recycled water remains stable.
</P>
<P>
The plant's handling capacity was doubled to one million tons
per day last October, after the completion of the stage two
project, which cost one billion yuan (about 125 million US dollars)
.
</P>
<P>
The plant supplies 200,000 tons of recycled water every day for
industrial use in eastern Beijing and 200,000-300,000 tons for
irrigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
