<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aventis to Produce Pesticide in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A transnational life science
corporation has established a joint venture in east China's
Hangzhou city to produce a new pesticide, it was announced here
today.
</P>
<P>
The new company, launched by Aventis CropScience and the
Hangzhou General Pesticide Plant with a total investment of 50
million euros (about 47 million US dollars), is the first
government-approved firm of its kind in China. Aventis CropScience
holds 75 percent of the company's stock shares.
</P>
<P>
The pesticide, mainly used for rice crops, was introduced in
1997 into China. Rice is the leading crop in this most-populous
country in the world.
</P>
<P>
The global sales value of rice pesticides totaled 1.4 billion
US dollars last year, following that of pesticides used for cotton
crops, according to Aventis CropScience, a major chemical and
biotech company under the world's leading life science group
Aventis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
