<HEADLINE> First Africa-Europe Summit Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Africa-Europe Summit, the first
and biggest gathering between the two continents to forge a new and
strategic relationship, opened here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak inaugurated the summit at the
Cairo International Convention Center shortly after 3:00 p.m. (1300
GMT).
</P>
<P>
Reviewing the changes and achievements made in Africa and the
help given by Europe to the poor continent, Mubarak stressed in his
speech that Africa should integret itself in the economic
globalization and get along with the international changes.
</P>
<P>
"So the African leaders should take decisions for the
establishment of African federation programs and parliament," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Portugese Prime Minister Antonio Guerres, whose country is
holding the EU presidency, also said in the ensuing address "it is
our profound wish that this most meaningful occasion should
represent a moment of renewal in the relationship between our two
neighboring continents."
</P>
<P>
Leaders from the two countinent came together with the hopes to
explore ways that the Europe's club of rich nations can help the
world's poorest continent join the global economy of the 21st
century, after decaces of post-colonial dependency.
</P>
<P>
Leaders from most of the 53 African states and the 15-member EU
attended the two-day summit to discuss political, economic and
development issues in Africa. 
</P>
