the northern Welioya area, killing eight rebels.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels, fighting for a separate homeland for minority
Tamils in Sri Lanka's north and east since 1983, have intensified
offensives last week in a bid to retake their former stronghold of
Jaffna peninsula. Hundreds of rebels and soldiers have been killed
or wounded in the week-long fighting. 
