The decision was made at an emergency meeting of mayors and
governors chaired by Prime Minister Park Tae-joon, who was
instructed by President Kim Dae-jung to lead the campaign to
prevent the epidemic, which has killed hundreds of livestock in
the country since late last month.
</P>
<P>
The government directed all public servants, workers and
farmers in the livestock breeding industry to join in the campaign
to head off the spread of the foot-and-mouth disease, which was
first discovered in Paju, Kyonggi Province last week and later in
Hongsong, South Chungchong Province, Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the government has ordered vaccines from Britain for
2 million heads of livestock, and will begin to provide preventive
shots to 11 million heads of cattle and pigs in the western part
of the nation.
</P>
<P>
Western areas are under intensive quarantine process as other
areas such as Yonki, South Chungchong Province, and Hwasong,
Kyonggi Province, saw similar cases that turned out to be negative
in the tests.
</P>
<P>
Japan and China's Taiwan have suspended import of livestock and
meat from South Korea while the United States and Australia halted
import of dairy products from the country.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean Quarantine Department has confirmed the
epidemic is O-type epidemic on livestock's mouth and hoof which
swept Taiwan one year ago.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that the epidemic has been found on the
Korean Peninsula since 1934. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
