<HEADLINE> China Bans Direct Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government issued a
circular today banning direct sales, which are staging a comeback
in the country.
</P>
<P>
The State Administration for Industry And Commerce asked local
law enforcers to crack down on various forms of direct sales,
including the "Network Double Earn", "Allied Chain", "Motivating
Sale" and "Rolling Sale".
</P>
<P>
The circular says that the operation will especially target
profiteers who prey on gullible people.
</P>
<P>
Units or persons who shift responsibility or dare to confront
the government will be punished, the circular warns.
</P>
<P>
Direct sales were introduced into China in the early 1990s by
some foreign companies, and soon became popular among people who
wanted to get rich overnight.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government eyes direct sales as illegal business
operations because they have created chaos in the market and
cheated people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
