<HEADLINE> China to Step Up Development of Resources in West </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- China intends to explore for
petroleum, natural gas, coal, rare metals and other mineral
resources in ten key areas in its western regions.
</P>
<P>
Exploration for minerals which are urgently needed and have a
significant bearing on the national economy will be accelerated in
the Tarim, Qaidam and Altay regions, on the upper reaches of the
Jinsha River, and on the middle and lower reaches of the Lancang
River, said Minister of Land and Resources Tian Fengshan.
</P>
<P>
Tian told Xinhua that in addition to mineral resources, China
will strengthen investigations into land and water resources in
the west to promote the development of the region, and to relieve
water shortages there.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized the importance of harmonious development between
resources utilization and environmental protection, and said the
ministry will make overall planning for exploiting mineral and
land resources in the western region.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he suggested the establishment of a geological
disaster forecasting system in the Three Gorges area.
</P>
<P>
There are about 39.3 million hectares of waste land suitable
for cultivation in the west, or more than half of the total
potential arable land in China. Among the 155 minerals found in
China, 123 can be found in the west, and over 20 mineral resources,
including natural gas, are abundant in the region. 
</P>
