CANBERRA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Australian sharemarket
climbed Monday more than 1.5 percent with strong gains in key blue-
chip stocks.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index, which has been expanded to 500
companies, was up by 49.9 points to 3,183.2 points at the close.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials was 74.4 points higher to 5,634.1 points
and the all resources, boosted by a seven percent jump in mining
giant Rio Tinto, finished up 37.1 points at 1,203.4 points.
</P>
