Bank pushing ahead 67 cents to 13.24 U.S. dollars, Westpac
increased 11.7 cents to 6.32, ANZ was up nine cents to 6.36 and
the Commonwealth Bank of Australia added 46.2 to 13.94.
</P>
<P>
Most local tech stocks were punished today. Melbourne IT, down $
1.12 to 7.96 U.S. dollars, was one of the worst performers today.
</P>
<P>
In the telco sector, Telstra gained 17.4 cents to 4.71 U.S.
dollars while Cable &AMP; Wireless Optus was steady at 4 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 919 million shares at a value of 848.4
million U.S. dollars. Falling stocks outpaced rising stocks 843 to
694, with 428 stocks steady. 
