<HEADLINE> Beijing University Merges with Beijing Medical University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- China's prestigious Beijing
University and the Beijing Medical University officially merged
here today.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin sent a congratulatory message to
the new university, which maintains the name Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that he felt happy that the two universities had
merged, with the goal of improving their comprehensive strength
and efficiency.
</P>
<P>
He noted that education is the basis for rejuvenating the
country, and its position in developing the economy and society is
irreplaceable.
</P>
<P>
A comprehensive university can play an important role in
cultivating talented people, spreading scientific information and
making innovations of knowledge, according to Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Jiang urged that Beijing University be constructed into a world-
class university by carrying forth both its revolutionary and
academic traditions.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing attended the merger rally, held at
Beijing University here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the two universities had been one in history, and
they have established a similar academic atmosphere and maintained
good relations.
</P>
<P>
The event is an important step for China to deepen the reform
of its university management system and to further the
readjustment of the distribution of higher learning institutions,
Li explained.
</P>
<P>
He said that the decision was made based on a detailed
feasibility study after examining first-rate overseas universities,
which are mostly comprehensive universities with medical colleges.
</P>
<P>
At the rally, Chen Zhili, minister of Education, announced the
appointment of Wang Debing, former president of Beijing Medical
University, as secretary of the Chinese Communist Party Committee
of Beijing University. Xu Zhihong will continue as president of
Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
Beijing University was established in 1898, and has been a
cradle for China's most important thinkers, philosophers and
educators. It spearheaded the famous May 4 movement of 1919 that
imported the concepts of science and democracy into China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
