<HEADLINE> China Launches Anti-Counterfeit-Money Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese authorities have
launched a six-month long nationwide campaign against criminals
engaged in forging false bank notes
</P>
<P>
This was announced here today at a State Council teleconference
on counterfeit money, which was attended by officials from the
People's Bank of China, the Ministry of Public Security, the
Supreme Court, the Supreme Procuratorate, and the State
Administration for Industry and Commerce.
</P>
<P>
The conference also announced that a joint action leading group
has been established by the five departments.
</P>
<P>
The campaign is mainly targeting counterfeit-money producers
and vendors in Guangdong, Zhejiang, Fujian, Hunan, Sichuan, Hubei,
Henan, Anhui, Shandong, Guizhou, Yunnan, and Hebei provinces,
Chongqing and Beijing municipalities, and the Guangxi and Inner
Mongolia ethnic autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
Each of these 16 provincial-level administrative areas should
appoint a leading government official to take charge of the local
campaign.
</P>
<P>
The localities will set up special squads to carry out the
campaign, with the police as the main force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
