<DOCNO> XIE20000403.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore to Review Banking Liberalization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Singapore will review the
progress of the banking liberalization program next year and
decide on further steps to open up the sector.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Prime Minister Lee Hsien Loong said this at a closed-
door seminar organized by the Monetary Authority of Singapore (MAS)
, the central bank, here.
</P>
<P>
Local banks will come under increasing pressure, not from MAS,
but from the rapid changes in technology and the market, he said.
</P>
<P>
The deputy prime minister, also chairman of MAS, unveiled last
May sweeping liberalization measures to increase foreign banks'
exposure to Singapore's domestic banking sector.
</P>
<P>
These include lifting a 40-percent limit on foreign ownership
in local banks and allowing more foreign banks into local retail
banking as well as wholesale banking.
</P>
<P>
Lee said the first priority for local banks is to upgrade their
capabilities and strengthen their management teams.
</P>
<P>
"This is the only way for them to hold their own in the new
environment, either by themselves or linked up with others in a
strategic alliance or merger," he said.
</P>
<P>
Banks also need to prepare themselves for new business
opportunities, especially e-banking, according to Lee.
</P>
<P>
MAS will continue discussing with local banks ways to increase
bank transparency further as greater disclosure will reinforce
corporate governance.
</P>
<P>
MAS is also reviewing the current minimum liquid assets and
minimum cash balance requirements imposed on banks and the capital
requirements for financial holding companies and banking groups.
</P>
<P>
It is also looking at bank involvement in non-financial
activities and the cross-holding structures typical of Singapore
banking groups,Lee said.
</P>
<P>
The aim is to minimize the risk of contagion and ensure that
management is focused on the core business of banking, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
