<HEADLINE> World-Class Ballroom Dancers Will Perform in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The well-known Brigham Young
University (BYU) Ballroom Dance Company of the United States will
be performing in China during a May tour.
</P>
<P>
Beijing dance fans will have the opportunity to watch the
American dancers at the beginning of the tour on May 11 and 12,
organizers from the Century Performance Corporation, one of China'
s influential theatrical agencies, announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The dance troupe will also be seen in Guangzhou in Guangdong
Province, Nanjing in Jiangsu Province, Shanghai, and Xi'an in
Shaanxi Province, the organizers said.
</P>
<P>
The BYU Ballroom Dance Company, known worldwide for its
exciting and energetic two-hour program, has won first prize at
the United States National Formation Dance Championships for 18
consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
The dancers aroused a heated response from Chinese audiences,
especially among young people, when it made its China debut 16
years ago.
</P>
<P>
According to critics, the dancers combine traditional formation
dances and standard ballroom steps with fresh choreography,
breathtaking lifts and spins, stunning costumes, and energetic
rhythms and melodies, in a show that delights and entertains
audiences of all kinds.
</P>
<P>
Formed in 1971, the Ballroom Dance Company has performed
throughout the United States and in 28 foreign countries,
featuring dances ranging from the Viennese Waltz to West Coast
swing.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Shan, senior project manager at Century Performance
Corporation, said the dance company's China performance will
include swing, Viennese waltzes, cha-cha, Argentine tango, comedy
tango, and rumba and quickstep.  
</P>
</TEXT>
