</P>
<P>
-- U.S. Secretary of Defense William Cohen will arrive in Egypt
Monday leading a high-level delegation for talks on military
cooperation with the Egyptian side. Cohen is currently on a
regional tour which includes Israel, Jordan, Qatar, Bahrain,
Kuwait, the United Arab Emirates, Saudi Arabia and Oman.
</P>
<P>
Al Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Portugal is aiming at enhancing trade ties with Egypt and the
rest of the Arab world. An economic delegation of the Arab-
Portuguese Chamber of Commerce has arrived in Cairo to meet Monday
with Egyptian businessmen and chambers of commerce. The meetings
will seek to facilitate trade between Egypt and Portugal and
encourage joint investments between the two countries.
</P>
