Al Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- A Pharaonic-era tomb dating back to the 17th or 18th century
B.C. has been uncovered in Egypt's largest oasis, Bahariya, the
Supreme Council for Antiquities said Sunday. The 26th dynasty tomb
contains a funerary chamber and a 3.5-meter-long sarcophagus.
Drawings on the tomb walls had been damaged by the Bawiti village's
sewerage system.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak on Monday will open a two-
day Africa-Europe Summit to be attended by around 37 heads of
state. The summit is designed to forge a new relationship between
the European Union (EU) and the world's poorest continent.
</P>
<P>
The EU, which initially favored focusing on political issues
such as democracy, governance, human rights and conflict
prevention, has accepted African insistence on putting trade and
debt relief issues high on the agenda. 
</P>
