<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Men Arrested for Planting Bombs in Ankara </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Two people, who left three pipe-
bombs in a trash can in Ankara's Haskoy district Monday morning,
were caught when one of the bombs exploded early.
</P>
<P>
The two men, who were planting bombs, were injured and rushed to
a nearby hospital for treatment, the Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The two, who were not identified, told the doctors they injured
themselves while cutting meat, but the doctors were not convinced.
The hospital police called the anti-terrorism teams, who arrested
the two suspects.
</P>
<P>
The two men confessed their crime during their first
interrogation. Later, bomb disposal experts denoted the
remaining two bombs left in the trash can. Investigation into the
incident was under way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
