<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Soar in Tokyo, Nikkei Hits Year's Closing High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices rose sharply in Tokyo
Monday following the release by the Bank of Japan (BOJ) of its
quarterly Tankan business confidence survey, with the key Nikkei
index hitting this year's closing high.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange jumped 389.67 points, or 1.92
percent, from last Friday's close to end at 20,726.99.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, surged 26.51 points, or 1.55 percent, to 1,
732.45.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 696.78 million
shares from last Friday's 514.36 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Mitsubishi Materials was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
The Tankan report for March released by the central bank shows
an improved business sentiment among Japan's large manufacturers
and nonmanufacturers.
</P>
<P>
The report underlined the recovering trend in Japan's economy,
making investors confident about buying stocks, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Expectations for the economic recovery boosted domestic demand-
related issues, they said.
</P>
<P>
Real estate firms, construction firms and banks were also
heavily bought, while export-oriented blue chips were up, with
concern about the strong yen receding following the BOJ's dollar-
supportive market intervention, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Losers included brokerage houses and wholesalers.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues on the First Section, gainers outpaced losers 764
to 500, with 120 issues closing unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
