injured during Thursday's Land Day riots in Sakhnin. A relative of
the woman said her death resulted from the tear gas used by
security forces to disperse demonstrators.
</P>
<P>
The woman had joined a picnic to mark the 24th Land Day and had
taken part in the annual event since 1976. Violence erupted when a
group of youngsters discovered a police unit at a concealed
observation point in the woods and began stoning them.
</P>
<P>
