<HEADLINE> Major Joint-Venture in Shenyang Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Shenyang Aerospace Mitsubishi
Motors Ltd., China's largest joint-venture in the field of
automobile motor production, has went into operation recently in
this capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The company, also the largest industrial joint venture in
Liaoning, has a registered capital of 738 million yuan (94.3
million US dollars) and total investment of 2.19 billion yuan (263.
7 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The company was jointly set up by China Aerospace and
Automobile Corporation, Shenyang Jianhua Motors Ltd., Mitsubishi
Motors Corporation, Mitsubishi Corporation, and MCIC holdings SDN.
BHD.
</P>
<P>
The company will have an annual production capacity of 150,000
automobile motors in seven types. 
</P>
