<HEADLINE> Feature: Candy Man's Sweet Mission (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"My father was recognized by people from all over the country
for his spirit of serving the people," he said. "I, along with my
colleagues, will continue to be so considerate to the customers
that they'll feel at home here."
</P>
<P>
Among the 200-plus brands of candy he sells is one named after
his father. According to the editor of the store's internal
newspaper "Flame Times", Li Ailing, Zhang Binggui Candy is the
star of the display. During the seven-day Spring Festival period
this year, a record 830 kg of Zhang Binggui Candy was sold, one
third of the counter's total sale.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Chaohe said that he spends a lot of his spare time
reading catering magazines and books to keep abreast of the latest
developments in the trade.
</P>
<P>
He said, "People should eat milk- or chocolate-based sweets in
winter to resist cold, and bigger people should go for fruit-juice
brands. I also strongly recommend orange and litchi types and, for
diabetics, sugar-free candies."  
</P>
</TEXT>
