<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Researchers Find Best Time to Detect Liver Cancer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese researchers have
discovered an early sensitive period for the clinical detection of
liver cancer and the best time to launch a general survey of the
disease.
</P>
<P>
Today's Science and Technology Daily reported that researchers
at the No. 2 Hospital attached to Jiangxi Medical College made
their discoveries during a major research program on the early
detection of liver cancer.
</P>
<P>
A researcher with the hospital said that based on comparison of
50,000 pieces of liver cancer data collected from three regions in
China at different latitudes, the research group has calculated
time parameters for the early diagnosis of liver cancer.
</P>
<P>
The three regions were chosen according to a liver cancer
morality map created by the tumor prevention office of the
Ministry of Health.
</P>
<P>
This research will also lay a theoretical basis for the
tumorized mechanism of liver calls, and the time and procedures
for controlling tumorized genes and detection of liver cancer.
</P>
<P>
These discoveries have passed the appraisal of experts from the
provincial science and technology commission of Jiangxi Province
in east China.
</P>
<P>
The experts believe the discoveries will be of great importance
to basic liver cancer clinical research.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000403.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Scientists Discover How Embryo is Infected with Hepatitis B Virus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have announced
their discovery of the cause of the Hepatitis B virus in embryos
in the mother's womb.
</P>
<P>
A research group at the No.4 Medical University of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army (PLA), led by Professor Xu Dezhong, found
that threatened abortion may cause damaged blood capillaries in
the placenta, and the blood of the mother with a high Hepatitis B
virus content may enter the embryo.
</P>
<P>
If the embryo is infected with the Hepatitis B virus in the
womb, the Hepatitis B vaccine will have no effect, scientists say.
</P>
<P>
The group started their research 1992, and the cause of this
particular infection was one of their key projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
