<HEADLINE> Shaq Blankets Knicks for MVP Stature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Shaquille O'Neal stunned the
Knicks to justify his candidancy for the MVP as the Los Angeles
Lakers stormed to a 106-82 victor over New York on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The superstar center started the game by rejecting Knicks
center Patrick Ewing's first layup attempt 30 seconds into the
game, and finished with 34 points, 12 rebounds, four assists and
five blocked shots.
</P>
<P>
In the first half, O'Neal bagged in 24 points for a 58-40 lead
at half break as the Lakers run steadily to their ninth
consecutive victory and 28th in 29 games.
</P>
<P>
Ewing led the Knicks with only 14 points.
</P>
<P>
In Miami, Jamal Mashburn scored 26 points to lead the Heat to
an 88-84 victory over the defending champion San Antonio Spurs
after Tim Duncan missed three crucial free throws down the stretch.
</P>
<P>
Miami moved 1 1/2 games ahead of second-place New York in the
Atlantic Division.
</P>
<P>
In Toronto, Jalen Rose scored 23 points and Sam Perkins went 6-
for-6 from 3-point range for a season-high 22 points to lead the
Indiana Pacers to a 104-83 thumping of the slumping Raptors.
</P>
<P>
Tracy McGrady had 24 points to lead the Raptors, who have lost
seven of their last eight.
</P>
<P>
In Portland, Steve Smith scored 21 points, Scottie Pippen added
18 as the Trail Blazers completed their first season sweep of the
Seattle SuperSonics in nine years with a 95-82 victory.
</P>
<P>
In Sacramento, Vlade Divac recorded his sixth career triple-
double and Chris Webber fell two assists shy of one of his own to
lead the Kings to a 117-95 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers.
</P>
<P>
Divac had 14 points, 11 rebounds and 11 assists, while Webber
finished with 26 points, 10 rebounds and eight assists.
</P>
<P>
At New Jersey, Jerry Stackhouse scored 34 points and Grant Hill
added 32 points, 12 rebounds and eight assists as the Detroit
Pistons pounded the Nets out of the playoff picture with a 113-92
drubbing.
</P>
<P>
At Golden State, the Milwaukee Bucks revived their playoff
hopes with a 117-113 win over the Warriors.
</P>
<P>
At Minnesota, the Phoenix Suns overcame a 13-point deficit in
the final period to edge the Timberwolves 87-86.
</P>
<P>
In Cleveland, the Chicago Bulls recorded only their 15th win of
the season with an 83-74 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers.
Only the L.A. Clippers have fewer wins than Chicago.
</P>
<P>
In Vancouver, the Dallas Mavericks soared to a 100-86 victory
over the Grizzlies. 
</P>
