<HEADLINE> Guizhou Constructs Electronic Component Production Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Construction of an electronic
component production base, the largest of its kind in western
China, has started in the Xintianzhai New and High Technology
Development Zone in Guiyang, capital of southwest China's Guizhou
Province.
</P>
<P>
Chen Qingjie, chairman of the China Zhenhua Electronics Group,
said that the base will cost 1 billion yuan (120 million U.S.
dollars) and will be completed in three to five years.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the base will produce 18 billion pieces of
electronic components by 2005, and output value will reach 5
billion yuan (602 million U.S. dollars) then. The sales income
will stand at 1.5 billion yuan (181 million U.S. dollars) and
taxes and profits, 350 million yuan (42.1 million U.S. dollars).
Foreign exchange earned from exports will amount to 100 million U.
S. dollars in 2005, according to Chen, who is also in charge of
construction of the production base.
</P>
<P>
The China Zhenhua Electronics Group, a major electronic
component developer and producer in China, achieved an output
value of 900 million yuan (108 million U.S. dollars) in 1999.
</P>
</TEXT>
