<HEADLINE> China, ROK Launch High-tech Animal Husbandry Joint Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Smooth cooperation between China and
the Republic of Korea (ROK) in agriculture in recent years has
encouraged ROK investors to put more money into related industries
in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on the establishment of an animal husbandry high-
tech zone has been signed between Laizhou City in Shandong
Province and the Korea National Livestock Cooperatives Federation.
</P>
<P>
Involving 120 million yuan (about 14.45 million US dollars) of
investment, the 333.33-hectare zone is divided into processing,
forage, cow-breeding, scientific and technological service zones,
and other specialties.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, Wu Shyue Bin, chairman of the board of the Korea
Dynasty Dairy Co. Ltd, set up a joint dairy processing plant with
Laizhou City. And the plant's annual sales volume already exceeded
12 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Encouraged by this successful project, eight more Korean
businessmen have expressed the intention to invest in animal
husbandry in Laizhou.  
</P>
