<HEADLINE> Shaanxi to Host High-Tech Investment Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Shaanxi Province in northwest China
will hold an international cooperation and investment meeting on
April 6 to promote the industrialization of its high-tech
achievements, local officials said.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi Province has 1,076 scientific research institutes and
850,000 technical personnel producing more than 2,000 scientific
research results annually.
</P>
<P>
But many of these scientific results cannot be industrialized
due to a lack of funds. By sponsoring the meeting, Shaanxi plans
to draw foreign and domestic investment and to promote its
scientific products and projects, the officials added.
</P>
<P>
To prepare for the event, Shaanxi Science and Technology
Committee organized three investment promotion teams to Japan, the
United States and Hong Kong and sent more than 100 invitations to
over 50 overseas companies.
</P>
<P>
So far, over 20 scientific institutes and high-tech companies
from the United States, Canada and Japan as well as Hong Kong and
Taiwan have acknowledged their participation in the meeting, the
officials noted.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 domestic investors also plan to attend the
gathering and they have already discussed cooperation programs
with some of Shaanxi's state and private high-tech enterprises,
the officials disclosed. 
</P>
