<HEADLINE> Chongqing to Open Air Route to Munich </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing Municipality in
southwest China will open an air route to the German city Munich
on May 18.
</P>
<P>
The new offering, first of its kind in western China, is aimed
to meet the increasing demand for air transport of tourists
between China and Germany, said a local aviation official.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing will be the third Chinese city after Beijing and
Shanghai to have direct air route to Germany, he said.
</P>
<P>
The flight service is to be operated by the LTU air company of
Germany, which features tourism routes, the official said, adding
that the German company also has the country's third largest
travel agency and forty luxury hotels worldwide.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that the new air route will
significantly boost tourism in western China. The company has so
far listed forty tourism programs including the Three Gorges,
China's largest water-conservancy project on the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The new international air route is the third one following
those to Nagoya and Bangkok for the municipality which is expected
to open an air route to Seoul this year. 
</P>
