<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Accession to WTO to Bring Hunan 200,000 Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- China's accession to the World
Trade Organization (WTO) will bring Hunan Province an additional
200,000 job opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Specialists at the Hunan Provincial Labor and Social Security
Bureau said that on China's accession to WTO, the agricultural
sector of this central Chinese province will see a drop of 300,000
jobs, but the industrial sector will see 400,000 extra jobs, and
the service trades will get 100,000 more job opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The experts noted that the main impact of China's accession to
the WTO on the province's employment situation might not be shown
in the increase or decrease of total jobs, but in the adjustment
of employment structure and the improvement in workers' quality.
</P>
<P>
Employment in agriculture and machine building will plummet,
but the chemical and light industries, construction and real
estate will see increases of 25,000, 200,000 and 220,000 jobs,
respectively, the experts said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
