<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Beijing University and Beijing Medical University (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing University is one of
China's top universities directly under the Ministry of Education.
</P>
<P>
Beijing University distinguishes itself by its rigorous style
of study, prominent academic standing and fruitful educational
achievements.
</P>
<P>
It has descended from the Metropolitan University (Jingshi
Daxutang) of the Qing Dynasty, which was a product of the Reform
Movement of 1898.
</P>
<P>
In May 1912, after the Revolution of 1911, the "Metropolitan
University" was renamed "Peking University". By 1919, the
university had become the country's largest institution of higher
learning, comprised of 14 departments and an enrollment of more
than 2,000 students.
</P>
<P>
During the Anti-Japanese War, Peking University moved to
Kunming, a city in southwest China's Yunnan Province, and formed,
together with Tsinghua University and Nankai University, the
National Southwest Associated University.
</P>
<P>
In 1946, after the victory of the War, Peking University
returned to Peiping (then the name of Beijing, or Peking). At that
time, the university had the schools of arts, science, law,
medicine, engineering, and agriculture, as well as a research
institute for the humanities. The total enrollment of students
grew to 3,000.
</P>
<P>
In order to carry on the revolutionary tradition of the May 4th
Movement, the university decided, after new China was founded in
1949, that the May 4th be set as the date on which to celebrate
the anniversary of its founding.
</P>
<P>
Beijing University has a beautiful campus, which is located at
Haidian District, an area in the western suburbs of Beijing
renowned in the old days for its gardens and parks. The campus,
known as "Yan Yuan".
</P>
<P>
To the north of the campus are the remains of the Yuan Ming
Yuan Palace, and to the west is the Summer Palace. The lovely
campus itself, with attractive scenery.
</P>
<P>
By November 1999, Beijing University had six colleges, 29
departments, 45 research institutes, 52 research centers, and
there are two national engineering research centers, 42 key
national disciplines, five national key laboratories.
</P>
<P>
The university has 3,000 teaching and researching staff, and 23,
000 domestic students and nearly 1,000 overseas students from over
60 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Beijing university, with a total construction area of 800,000
square meters of land, boasts the country's fifth largest library,
with 4.4 million books.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
