<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed higher here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 43 points higher at 2,097 with a
turnover of 115.5 million NZ dollars (57.4 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
It was a good day for Fletcher stocks, with both Energy and
Paper rising 32 cents to 480 and 170 cents respectively, Building
up 7 to 225 cents and Forests 6 to 59 cents.
</P>
<P>
Among other leading stocks, Carter Holt Harvey gained 18 cents
to 192 cents, Tower 15 to 500 cents, Telecom 14 to 925 cents and
Contact Energy 1 to 268 cents.
</P>
<P>
Auckland Airport fell 5 cents to 238 cents and Air New Zealand-
A 4 to 188 cents.
</P>
<P>
There were 70 rises and 41 falls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
