<HEADLINE> Qinghua University Supports Science, Education Development in West </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Qinghua University, one of China's
most prestigious institutions of higher learning, has signed
cooperation contracts with enterprises and research institutes in
western China to support science and education development in the
region.
</P>
<P>
Under these agreements, Qinghua will help upgrade the
technologies and equipment of traditional industries in the
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The university will set up working and research stations for
Masters and Postdoctoral degrees in Xinjiang, and will help
establish long-distance education network in the region.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the university has signed a contract with Chinese
Academy of Engineering Physics in Mianyang in Sichuan Province to
train 90 professionals working in advanced military technology
over the next three years. Graduates will be required to work for
the academy for at least five years after graduating from Qinghua.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leadership recently urged all localities to take
every opportunity to accelerate economic development in western
China, and development of science and technology, education, and
speeding up the cultivation of trained personnel have been listed
as the major tasks for western development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
