<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Promote Environmentally Conscious  Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will launch a campaign to
promote environmentally conscious tourism, as a response to the
ASEAN Environmental Year 2000, a senior Thai science, technology
and environment ministry official said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Saksit Tridech, secretary-general of the Office of
Environmental Policy and Planning, was quoted by Thailand News
Agency (TNA) as saying that the campaign will be jointly organized
by the Thai government and the state-run Tourism Authority of
Thailand (TAT).
</P>
<P>
He said all member countries of the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN) will organize activities focusing on
environmental conservation to join the ASEAN Environmental Year
2000 campaign.
</P>
<P>
Thai Science, Technology and Environment Minister Arthit
Urairat will fly to Brunei Monday to attend the inaugural ceremony
of the ASEAN campaign on April 4.
</P>
<P>
Chatri Chuayprasit, director-general of the Department of
Environmental Quality Promotion, was also quoted by TNA as saying
that the Thai campaign will be officially launched in late April.
The campaign is aimed not only to promote tourism industry in
Thailand but also create the environmental conservation
consciousness among tourists and the general public to help
achieve the ASEAN goal of sustainable development with retaining
natural resources as well as national arts and cultures, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
