<HEADLINE> Trinidad Beats Dominicans in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Helped by two penalties,
Trinidad won its Caribbean zone second round first leg 3-0 against
the Dominican Republic in a World Cup qualifier in Port of Spain
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Without top player Dwight Yorke, Trinidad spent 68 minutes
before Arnold Dwarika converted from the the penalty spot
following a foul on Sherwin Julien.
</P>
<P>
Dwarika also scored Trinidad's third from another penalty in
the last minute.
</P>
<P>
In between, Angus Eve, who plays for English third division
club Chester City, scored Trinidad's second from a rebound.
</P>
<P>
If Trinidad qualifies, its next tie is almost certain to be
against Haiti, who smashed nine goals against Bahamas in Port-of-
Prince on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Barbados also appeares to go into the next round after a 3-1
win away to Aruba on Saturday night in their first leg match.
</P>
<P>
Cuba beat Surinam 1-0 in Havana with a goal by Osmin Hernandez.
</P>
<P>
In Central America, El Salvador beat Guatemala 1-0 away to go
top of group A with a maximum six points from two games.
</P>
<P>
Panama also made it maximum six points from two games in group
B thanks to a 1-0 win at home to Honduras. The only goal came in
the 69th minute from Spanish-based striker Julio Dely Valdes.
</P>
<P>
Mexico, Costa Rica, Jamaica, United States and Canada have a
bye to the last twelve. 
</P>
</TEXT>
