<HEADLINE> Xinhua Commentary Urges New Methods of Ideological Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A commentary of China's official
news agency Xinhua has called for exploring new methods of
ideological work that are fit to the country's new situation.
</P>
<P>
"Ideological and political work has been a good tradition and
political advantage of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC)", the
commentary said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few decades, the CPC has accumulated a lot of
experiences and created many effective methods, which played an
important role in both the revolution and the country's
construction.
</P>
<P>
Despite of many advantages, the party's ideological work faces
challenges from the Western values, diversification of economic
factors and interests, as well as new ways of information
acquisition such as the Internet, it said.
</P>
<P>
"Ideological and political work has to be centered around the
country's economic construction, and serve the overall interests
of reform, development and stability," the commentary explained.
</P>
<P>
It is imperative to combine ideological work with solutions to
practical issues of the masses, it stated.
</P>
<P>
To care for the masses has been a good tradition of the party,
the commentary said, adding ideological work can only become
effective when sincere efforts are taken to tackle with issues
that the masses care about.
</P>
<P>
The commentary also noted that more emphasis has to be devoted
to management if the ideological work hopes to become more
effective. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
