<HEADLINE> ASEAN Culture, Information Meeting Opens in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The 35th meeting of the Committee
on Culture and Information (COCI) of the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN) opened here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The five-day meeting is attended by representatives of ten
ASEAN member nations, ASEAN Secretariat and Australia.
</P>
<P>
Participants will approve the draft papers on ASEAN cultural
heritage, review the implementation of cultural and information
plans, and discuss future programs made at the ASEAN Summit and
meetings of the permanent committee.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the ASEAN COCI meeting,
Myanmar Minister of Culture U Win Sein pledged the country's
commitment to the belief that the meeting can help disseminate
information about unity in diversity in the region.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the COCI meeting will not only strengthen the
cooperation among ASEAN member countries but also enhance the
knowledge about Myanmar and its people.
</P>
<P>
The 34th ASEAN COCI meeting was held in Manila, the Philippines
in May 1999.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN groups Brunei, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia,
Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
</TEXT>
