<HEADLINE> Philippoussis Withdraws from Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Mark Philippoussis Monday decided
to skip the Davis Cup tennis quarter-final between Australia and
Germany in Adelaide as he suffered an injured left calf muscle.
</P>
<P>
Philippoussis, 23, sustained the injury two weeks ago in Indian
Wells, California.
</P>
<P>
"It's unfortunate that Mark can't be here but we have to think
long term, and it's important not to put him at risk this weekend,
" said Australian captain John Newcombe.
</P>
<P>
Newcombe has drafted Wayne Arthurs into the team as
Philippoussis' replacement, and Pat Rafter is likely to play the
Davis Cup singles alongside Lleyton Hewitt following his comeback
from shoulder surgery.
</P>
