<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: China's Exports to NZ in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Following are latest facts and
figures about China's major exports to New Zealand in January this
year, provided by the General Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
Export of machines, electronic goods, audiovisual equipment and
relevant parts and accessories stood at 3.642 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Export value of shoes, caps, umbrella, feather products and
artificial flower was 2.491 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Export of textile materials and products was valued at 18.188
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Export of metal products was 1.426 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
