<HEADLINE> Japanese Prime Minister Suffers Stroke </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi
has suffered a stroke and is being treated in the intensive care
unit at a Tokyo hospital, Chief Cabinet Secretary Mikio Aoki said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Aoki, the top government spokesman, was appointed as acting
prime minister by the Japanese government.
</P>
<P>
Obuchi was taken to a hospital in Tokyo early Sunday morning
after falling ill at his official residence. 
</P>
