<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: China's Top 10 Provinces, Municipalities in Trade (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua)-- Following are the latest statistics
of China's ten largest provinces and municipalities in trade in
January this year, provided by the General Administration of
Customs:
</P>
<P>
-- Guangdong Province boasted a total trade volume of 13.082
billion U.S. dollars, up 45.9 percent from the same period last
year. Exports reached 7.400 billion U.S. dollars, up 62.3 percent,
while imports increased 28.8 percent to 5.682 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Shanghai reported a total trade of 3.681 billion U.S.
dollars, up 98.9 percent from the same period last year. Exports
totaled 1.546 billion dollars, up 47.5 percent, with imports
rising 166 percent to 2.135 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Beijing saw a total trade volume rise of 63.5 percent over
the same period last year, to 1.632 billion U.S. dollars. Exports
increased 27.8 percent to 459.769 million U.S. dollars, while
imports rose 83.7 percent to 1.172 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Jiangsu Province reported a total foreign trade volume of 2.
997 billion U.S. dollars, up 86.7 percent from the same period
last year. Exports were 1.428 billion dollars, up 61.2 percent;
while imports reached 1.569 billion U.S. dollars, up 118.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Shandong Province reported a 23.4 percent growth in total
trade volume over the same period last year, to reach 1.631
billion U.S. dollars. Exports came to 953.6 million U.S. dollars,
up 23.8 percent, while imports increased 22.8 percent to 677.712
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
