percent from the same period last year to reach 1.568 billion U.S.
dollars. Exports grew 29.3 percent to 925.594 million U.S. dollars,
and imports increased 20.8 percent to 642.040 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Liaoning Province registered a total foreign trade of 911.
809 million U.S. dollars, up 9.3 percent from the same period last
year. Exports reached 420.607 million U.S. dollars, down 3.1
percent, while imports rose 22.7 percent to 491.202 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Tianjin's trade volume rose 36.6 percent to 1.297 billion U.
S. dollars, with exports standing at 630.942 million U.S. dollars,
up 11.4 percent, and imports climbing 74.0 percent to 665.619
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Hebei Province saw 380.747 million U.S. dollars in total
trade volume, up 44.7 percent from the same period last year.
Exports rose 26.2 percent to 224.259 million U.S. dollars, and
imports were 156.488 million U.S. dollars, up 83.4 percent.
</P>
