<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Trade of China's Five Special Economic Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Following are facts and figures
about foreign trade of China's five Special Economic Zones (SEZ)
in January this year, provided by the General Administration of
Customs:
</P>
<P>
The Xiamen SEZ reported a total foreign trade turnover of 538.
668 million U.S. dollars, up 32.5 percent over the same period
last year. Exports rose 37.7 percent to 308.702 million U.S.
dollars, with imports rising 26.1 percent to 229.966 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen SEZ reported a total foreign trade turnover of 2.
410 billion U.S. dollars, up 29.3 percent. Exports grew by 21.6
percent to 1.173 billion U.S. dollars with imports rising 37.5
percent to 1.238 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Zhuhai SEZ reported a total foreign trade turnover of 511.
707 million U.S. dollars, up 40.5 percent. Exports increased by 42.
9 percent to 231.337 million U.S. dollars, with imports up 38.6
percent to reach 280.370 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Shantou SEZ reported a total foreign trade turnover of 529.
129 million U.S. dollars, up 203.3 percent. Exports surged 587.3
percent to 411.599 million U.S. dollars, with imports rising 2.6
percent to 117.531 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Hainan SEZ reported a total foreign trade volume of 98.413
million U.S. dollars, up 19.6 percent. Exports climbed 57.0
percent to 51.956 million U.S. dollars, with imports down 5.6
percent to 46.457 million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
