<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China's Guangxi Exports More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 3 (Xinhua) --South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region did 258 million U.S. dollars in foreign trade in
the first two months of the year.
</P>
<P>
Information from the regional foreign trade and economic
cooperation bureau noted that the volume represents a rise of 14.3
percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Out of the total foreign trade volume, exports made up 206
million U.S. dollars, up 40 percent from that of last year.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, the autonomous region approved overseas-
financed projects with contracted investment of 122 million U.S.
dollars, of which, 75.14 million U.S. dollars was placed in. Both
figures show sharp increases over that of last year.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi, with a territory of 230,000 sq km, is home to 11 major
ethnic groups, including Zhuang, Miao, Yao, Maonan and Gin. The
region has more favorable geographic conditions for doing foreign
trade than its other neighbors as it faces the Beibu Gulf in the
south border. 
</P>
</TEXT>
