<BODY>
<HEADLINE> On-line Drug Store Sells Contraceptives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 3 (Xinhua) -- "On-line Eden"--(http://202.102.
231.54/yidianyuan)-- is the first on-line store selling
contraceptives and other sexual aids set up by the Pingdingshan
Medicine and Trade Center.
</P>
<P>
In the first two days, five people have bought products on-line.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Dongjie, a chief official with the Center, said that the
reason for founding such a on-line store is because "we have
observed that many consumers are usually embarrassed to buy sexual
aids directly from drug stores."
</P>
<P>
The on-line store is projected to protect consumers privacy and
provides a convenient way for shopping. Sexual aids and other
medicines bought via the website can be delivered directly to
buyers, normally within an hour if the buyers are in Pingdingshan.
</P>
<P>
About 341 kinds of medicines, classified in six categories,
including contraceptives and medicines to treat and cure venereal
diseases, are available in the shop.
</P>
<P>
Unlike the western people, Chinese are generally shy or
conservative of talking about sex-related topics, even though the
government has been promoting sex education in schools across
China over the past decade.
</P>
<P>
When China's first contraceptive-selling store opened
cautiously in Beijing about a decade ago, it had to be closed from
time to time because of strong opposition from local residents.
</P>
</TEXT>
