<HEADLINE> Sampras Wins Ericsson Open Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Pete Sampras won his first
title of the year after beating Gustavo Kuerten of Brazil in the
Ericsson Open final at Key Biscayne, Florida, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Sampras won the four-set thriller 6-1, 6-7 (2-7), 7-6 (7-5), 7-
6 (10-8) in three hours and 18 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Sampras took a 6-2 lead in the final tiebreaker but made four
errors to make the score 6-6. After holding another match point
at 7-6, Sampras double-faulted and then hit a backhand return to
lead at 8-7.
</P>
<P>
Kuerten made a mistake as his forehand passing shot clipped the
net cord and sailed long. That mistake gave Sampras the victory
and he raised both arms in jubilation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
