<HEADLINE> Asian Boxers Enters Second Competing Day in Qualifying Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The 3rd Asian qualifying boxing
tournament for Olympic Games 2000 goes into the second day Sunday
with no surprise, but more foul-outs.
</P>
<P>
Thai bantamweight Choptipat Wongprate defeated Roel Laguna from
the Philippines with a 18-9 score, and joined the other 23 winners
to the second round of the
final leg of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Another Thai bantamweight Wijarn Polrit has entered
quarterfinal in the previous day. Choptipat, who twice suffered
defeats in the first and second leg of the Asian qualifying
tournament, is very determined this time.
</P>
<P>
"I am well prepared and very keen to earn my place for the
Millennium Games," said Choptipat, who has changed his name for
better luck. Six boxers are fouled out of the ring by the
referees, one more than the beginning day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
