<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rostock Away from Relegaion Zone, Stuttgart Wins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Hansa Rostock lift themselves out
of relegation zone by holding Werder Bremen 1-1 while Stuttgart
beat Kaiserslautern 2-1 in the German Bundesliga on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Peter Wibran gave Rostock the lead at the 35th minute, only to
see Marco Bode hit the equalizer less than one minute later.
</P>
<P>
But the draw was enough to lift Rostock out of the relegation
zone as they now have 30 points to their credit. Frankfurt
returns again into relegation zone.
</P>
<P>
In the other match played on Sunday, Stuttgart beat
Kaiserslautern 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Kaiserslautern took the lead at the 26th minute when French
international Youri Djorkaeff slamed home a free kick by Mario
Basler.
</P>
<P>
Two minutes later, Sean Dundee equalized for Stuttgart and
Krassimir Balakov converted a penalty kick at the 77th minute.
</P>
</TEXT>
