<DOCNO> XIE20000403.0345 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PNA, EU Sign Cooperative Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) and the European Union (EU) on Monday agreed to jointly
launch an air cargo section at the Gaza International Airport
(GIA).
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Palestinian Minister of Planning and
International Cooperation Nabil Sha'ath and Chief of Civil Aviation
Authority Brigadier Faiz Zaidan and the EU commissioner for foreign
relations, Christopher Patin.
</P>
<P>
Under the deal, the EU will provide the PNA with 25 million
euros (23.8 million U.S. dollars) to establish the air cargo
section within 10 months. The project will confirm the independence
of the Palestinian export-import movement from Israeli airlines.
</P>
<P>
The deal will facilitate the export-import movement between
Palestine and the world countries, according to Sha'ath who praised
the E.U. role in the Middle East peace process and in developing
the Palestinian economy.
</P>
<P>
Palestine received up to 350 million U.S. dollars out of 700
million in aid from the EU and the European Investment Bank over
the last six years, Sha'ath said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the EU official noted that the initiation of the air
transport section would contribute to the growth of the Palestinian
economy.
</P>
<P>
Patin, who started his visit to Palestine on Monday, said the
visit is important for the EU that has strong relations with the
PNA.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out the keenness of the EU on accelerating the
procedures of the accord implementation.
</P>
<P>
The GIA plays in important role in connecting Palestine with not
only the EU but also the world at large, he said, adding that the
airport will contribute greatly to the revival of Palestine in
various fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
