<HEADLINE> Nasdaq Index Suffers Deepest One-day Point Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The technology heavy Nasdaq
composite index on Wall Street suffered the deepest one-day point
drop in its 29-year history.
</P>
<P>
According to preliminary calculations, the composite closed
down 348,96 or 7.4 percent at 4,223.87, surpassing a loss of 229
points on January 4 this year.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly higher. The Dow Jones
industrial average rose 300.01 at 11,221.93 and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index rose 7.39 at 1,505.97. 
</P>
