<DOCNO> XIE20000403.0348 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rio de Janeiro Stock Market to Suspend Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Rio de Janeiro
stockmarket (BVRJ) will suspend operations from April 28 until
June 3 this year, the market announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
BVRJ superintendent Sergio Berardi said that after September 3,
the Sao Paulo and Rio de Janeiro share markets will be
concentrated in Sao Paulo.
</P>
<P>
According to Berardi, these measures form part of the
unification accord between the Sao Paulo and Rio de Janeiro stock
exchange markets reached in January 2000.
</P>
<P>
The change won't affect the financial situation of the Rio de
Janeiro center, he said.
</P>
<P>
The BVRJ director recognized that about 50 percent of the
current stock market officials will lose their posts.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the Sao Paulo and Rio de Janeiro stock
exchanges announced Monday the buying of the Argentina Stockmarket
electronic system, which will be applied on Brazil's two main
stock markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
