<DOCNO> XIE20000403.0349 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Gets Trade Surplus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Brazil got 42 million dollars of
trade surplus, lower than February's 78 million dollars, said the
Ministry of Development, Industry and Foreign Trade on Monday.
</P>
<P>
 The accumulated trade balance reached 26 million dollars in
the first quarter of this year, compared with 816 million dollars
of deficit in the same period of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Brazil exported 12.048 billion dollars in the first quarter
of this year, increasing by 19.9 percent against 10.045 billion
dollars of the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
 At the same time, Brazil's imports reached 12.022 billion
dollars, increasing by 10.7 percent over the first three months of
last year, which was 10.861 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
