<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ELN Attacks Colombia Highway Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Guerrillas Monday destroyed a
bridge and damaged another with dynamite, while military patrols
made attempts on five others on the highway joining Bogota and
Medellin, reported military sources.
</P>
<P>
Guerrillas of the National Liberation Army (ELN) loaded with
explosives three buses whose drivers were forced to halt on the
affected bridges, including Vallesol, close to San Luis locality.
</P>
<P>
In this zone confrontations have been registered between
insurgents and troops from the army's 4th brigade, whose patrols
stopped guerrillas from attacking the five other bridges in the
same area, said an official spokesperson. The rebels forced the
closing of the road between San Luis and Samana localities.
</P>
<P>
To these attacks can be added a gigantic exodus of peasants of
Antioquia department toward urban areas of several localities, in
face of threats from paramilitary groups.  
</P>
</TEXT>
