<HEADLINE> China to Expand Cooperation With Kenya in Road Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- China is ready to further promote
cooperation in road construction with Kenya, a visiting senior
Chinese official said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Chinese companies are not only good at implementing projects,
but also good at designing, manufacturing mechanical equipment as
well as management, " Chinese Vice Minister of Communications Li
Juchang said when he held talks with Kenyan Minister of Roads and
Public Works Andrew Kiptoon.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and Kenya enjoy very good relations in many
areas, which are believed to be boosted further following the
China-Africa Cooperation Forum to be held in Beijing this October.
</P>
<P>
The vice-minister also briefed Kiptoon on great progress China
has made in road construction over the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China has boasted a good road network totaling
1.35 million kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Kiptoon said that Chinese contractors have undertaken several
projects in Kenya, which especially facilitate the development of
rural areas in the east African country.
</P>
<P>
Kiptoon expressed the belief that the strong ties between the
two countries will be conducive to common prosperity in the
future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
