<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 100 AIDS Counsellors Trained in Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- About 110 AIDS counsellors and
anti-AIDS club representatives in secondary and tertiary
institutions have been sensitized on AIDS prevention by the
Jerusalem AIDS project, Rwanda News Agency reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Silas Nzabonakura, who is in charge of information, education
and communication in the national AIDS control program, said that
the Jerusalem AIDS project aims to fight AIDS through education.
</P>
<P>
It has provided education materials about AIDS in a bid to
strengthen ties with Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
Participants were sensitized on the role of education in
fighting AIDS, health education and sexuality and the aspect of
behavioral change, Nzabonakura said.
</P>
<P>
AIDS is one of the leading causes of death in Rwanda. The major
 constraints to HIV/AIDS control in Rwanda include stigma and
discrimination against people with AIDS. Illiteracy remains a
stumbling block to AIDS education.
</P>
<P>
More than 400,000 Rwandans are living with HIV and about
180,000 of them have developed AIDS. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000403.0361 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NATO, World Bank to Back Romania in Re-training Redundants from Army </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Romania would benefit from NATO
and World Bank support in the re-training of the people who are
going to be made redundant from the Army, President of NATO's
Economic Committee Georges Daniel said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Georges Daniel made the remark when received by Romanian
National Defence Minister Sorin Frunzaverde.
</P>
<P>
He said the North-Atlantic Alliance was willing to help Romania
in its integration efforts, in solving the problems related to the
management of the resources for defence.
</P>
<P>
The President of NATO's Economic Committee told the Romanian
Defence Minister that NATO and the World Bank wished to assist
Romania and Bulgaria in the professional re-training of the
persons who are going to be made redundant from the Army. The
programme could start at the end of the current year or early next
year.
</P>
<P>
Georges Daniel is in Bucharest now to attend an international
seminar on "Economic aspects of management of resources earmarked
for defence expenses in conformity with methodologies used by NATO
member countries", organized by the Romanian Ministry of National
Defence, the Romanian Foreign Ministry and the Romanian Ministry
of Finance.
</P>
<P>
Sorin Frunzaverde said that he was confident the seminar would
contribute to a better understanding of the problems the Romanian
Army faces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
