<HEADLINE> U.S. House Condemns Austria's Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The resolution, passed by a voice vote, pointed out that Joerg
Haider, the leader of the Freedom Party, praised Nazis in the past,
called Waffen SS veterans "decent people" and decried the "over-
foreignization" of Austria..
</P>
<P>
The House members also expressed their "profound regret and
dismay" at the joining of the Freedom Party in Austria's coalition
government.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the resolution urged the White House and the
administration to make clear to Austria U.S. concern about the
inclusion of a party associated with xenophobic, racist policies.
</P>
<P>
In reaction to the inclusion of the Freedom Party in the new
Austrian government, the U.S. administration expressed its concern
and called its ambassador back earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU) cut off its political relations with
Austria while Israel has withdrawn its ambassador to protest the
Freedom Party's role in the government. 
